{title: Christmas Time Back Home}
{artist: The Country Gentlemen}
{composer: Written by John Duffey and Ann Streeter}

[G]Back up in the mountains in the old home town of [C]mine
There's not a brighter [G]time of year than that of Christmas [D7]time
The [G]bells in the little church they'll all begin to [C]chime
Telling all for [G]miles around [D7]rejoice its Christmas [G]time
[C]Christmas bells are ringing I [G]hear their chimes so sweet
The carolers are singing now I hear them in the [D7]street
Out[G]side the white snow falling inside my heart I [C]find
A world of joy and [G]peace on earth back [D7]home at Christmas [G]time
A candle in each window they give a golden [C]glow
While out among the [G]shimmering pines lights sparkle in the [D7]snow
And [G]through the lonely mountain tops the wind shrill echoes [C]sigh
For peace on earth good[G]will toward men and [D7]faith that will not [G]die
Repeat #2
High above our little town so bright to be so [C]fine
There shines upon the whole [G]wide world His gift our guiding [D7]star
[G]Every one in each home can feel a peace of [C]land
And know the joy the [G]Yuletide brings to [D7]all at Christmas [G]time
Repeat #2
[C]A world of joy and [G]peace on earth back [D7]home at Christmas [G]time